To enable Hibernate mode in Windows 10,


Go to Settings > System > Power & sleep.
Scroll down on the right-hand side and click the “Additional power settings” link.
That will open Power Options in the classic Control Panel.
In Power Options, click on "Choose what the power button does" or "Choose what closing the lid does".
to add in start menu -- click on " change settings that are not currently available" -- then mark to hibernate.
also for hardware power button Select "Hibernate" and click "Save Changes".
